Description:
Designer inner-city warehouse living
An exclusive boutique development in Collingwood's iconic Foy & Gibson precinct sets the scene for this New York-style townhouse enjoying absolute privacy, luxury and inner-city practicality. One of only 16 in a serene environment defined by its grand open-roof foyer and bold industrial cues, the townhouse itself boasts one extra-large bedroom (built-in robes) and deluxe ensuite bathroom, gourmet stone-bench kitchen with soft-close drawers and finest appliances, plus a light-filled open living/dining area complete with loft-style study. Vaulted ceilings, exposed beams and solid brickwork add to the appeal, as well as polished hardwood floors, Euro laundry, intercom/secure entry and lower-level parking space. Modern living wrapped in heritage style, Smith Street/Gertrude Street cafes and restaurants, cosmopolitan shopping precincts and city-bound trams are all within easy reach.
Agent - hockingstuart
Charles Atkins : 0405 287 112
Insights: 12/76 Oxford Street, COLLINGWOOD VIC 3066 was last sold in 2015 and 49 other 1 bedroom unit in COLLINGWOOD have recently been sold.

Description:
MAGNIFICENT VICTORIAN, PRIME POSITION
This classic Victorian terrace cottage combines beautiful ornate period features and contemporary living aspects with evident charm and success. Perfect for those looking to enter the market or downsize with style it offers wonderfully high ceilings in two robed bedrooms, one with private outdoor sitting area, serviced by a sparkling central bathroom. From there back the property has been renovated superbly, timber floors adorn the satisfyingly spacious open-plan kitchen/dining/living zone, with French doors to sideway. Enormous bi-fold doors unveil decking and a great brick outdoor entertaining area, low-maintenance garden plus ROW remote controlled roller-door access. This neat home offers an enormous attic storage space, stainless steel appliances and is ideally located just moments from shops, transport and the vibrant Johnston St cafe and nightlife scene.

Description:
Contemporary style with industrial edge
Towering ceilings, vast open spaces and an abundance of natural light define this spectacular warehouse conversion ideally situated in Collingwood's iconic Foy & Gibson precinct. Complete with secure parking space and private entrance directly onto Cambridge Street, this stunning three-level home boasts 2 large bedrooms (both with vaulted ceilings) and open study area, deluxe central bathroom, enormous open-design living/dining area and stylish Smeg kitchen with walk-in pantry/laundry. Other stand-out features include hydronic heating and split-system air conditioning, exposed beams and brickwork, versatile storage spaces and more. Moments from Smith Street's vibrant cafe and restaurant precinct, Gertrude Street's boutique shops, public transport options and impressively close proximity to the CBD.

Description:
7% Net Return and Low OC fees!!!
With secure tenants in place until February 2016 this investment ticks all the boxes! Currently returning $1,195 per calendar month you will start enjoying the returns on this property from the moment you take ownership.
Features Include:
- Attractive layout with central bathroom and open plan kitchen/living
- Comes fully furnished, offering convenience to tenants and allowing you to achieve a top rent
- Corner, top floor, light a bright apartment with ideal Northwest aspect
- Offers a gross return of approx. 9.55%
- One of the larger layouts in the complex
- Extremely low vacancy rates with virtually no vacant days in the last 5 years.
- Beautiful red brick building (circa 1925) with high ceilings
Location is second to none, only a short walk to popular Smith and Gertrude St and close to RMIT, ACU and Melbourne Universities. You also have trams and buses right out front and Parliament railway station a short stroll away.
***Please note this accommodation is exclusive to student occupiers***
All of the above features ensure you will enjoy very low vacancy rates. This hassle free investment is a must inspect. Call Bob Budd to arrange a viewing today.

Description:
CONTEMPORARY STYLE, VICTORIAN INSPIRED
Perfectly positioned, this balconied terrace makes a sound investment or ideal low-maintenance lifestyle opportunity in one of inner-Melbourne's most vibrant pockets. Beyond its period-style facade complete with lacework and tessellated tiles, the home's immaculate interior highlights two double bedrooms (with robes), main bathroom and powder room (second WC), open lounge and dining areas complemented by a central kitchen. Add to this gas heating and split-system air conditioning, separate laundry, plus a private undercover courtyard complete with secure carport via rollerdoor (remote-controlled) to Palmer Lane. Easy access to Victoria Park Station, Johnston Street buses, Smith Street trams, cafes and restaurants - city living at its best! Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
